SIMPLE: axial
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Axial
<hw>Ax"i*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to an axis; of the nature of, or resembling, an axis; around
an axis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To take on an <qex>axial</qex>, and not an equatorial,
direction.</q> <rj><qau>Nichol.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Belonging to the axis of the
body; <as>as, the <ex>axial</ex> skeleton</as>; or to the axis of any
appendage or organ; <as>as, the <ex>axial</ex> bones</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Axial line</b></col> <fld>(Magnetism)</fld>, <cd>the line
taken by the magnetic force in passing from one pole of a horseshoe
magnet to the other.</cd> <rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Axially</ent>⟦br⟧
